Python Variables

- Names store references to values: x = 5
- Python picks the type from the value (dynamic typing); you can reassign a new type to the same name.
- Casting: str(), int(), float(), bool() when you need a specific type.
- type(x) shows the type of a value.
- Rules for names: letters, digits, underscore; cannot start with a digit; no spaces; case-sensitive.
- Assign several at once: x, y, z = 1, 2, 3

Global variables (module level) vs local (inside functions) is covered again in later lessons.

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_variables.asp

